## Troubleshooting

<AccordionGroup>
<Accordion title="OpenAPI documentation not generating">
**Symptoms**: Blank page or missing API documentation when using `openapi:` frontmatter

**Solutions**:
- Verify the `openapi` value exactly matches a path and method in `openapi.json`
- Check for JSON syntax errors in your OpenAPI specification
- Ensure the path includes the HTTP method: `GET /users/{id}` not `/users/{id}`
- Validate your OpenAPI spec using online validators
- Check browser console for JavaScript errors
</Accordion>

<Accordion title="Code blocks not appearing in right column">
**Symptoms**: Code examples appear inline instead of in the right sidebar

**Solutions**:
- Ensure `num` field is set in frontmatter
- Verify you're using `<CodeGroup>` components, not plain code fences
- Check that `num` value matches or exceeds the number of `<CodeGroup>` blocks
- Confirm you're using `api:` frontmatter (not `openapi:`)
</Accordion>

<Accordion title="Page not appearing in navigation">
**Symptoms**: Documentation page exists but doesn't show in sidebar

**Solutions**:
- Add the page path to `docs.json` in the appropriate group
- Verify the path is relative to `src/app/(pages)/` without `.mdx` extension
- Check for JSON syntax errors in `docs.json`
- Ensure the page has valid frontmatter with a `title` field
- Restart the development server after modifying `docs.json`
</Accordion>

<Accordion title="Curly braces causing errors in code examples">
**Symptoms**: MDX parsing errors or missing code content

**Solutions**:
- Wrap code content in template literals: `{` backtick `code here` backtick `}`
- Required for JSON examples and any code containing `{` or `}` characters
- Applies to all code inside `<CodeSnippet>` components
</Accordion>
</AccordionGroup>

